I have to be honest, this game is great. It has a great concept and premise. But it's actually not perfect. I mean it's choice-based, I'm choosing what I'm saying, but the game is still going the way that it's meant to. "Simulacra" is more of like an interactive reading kind of simulation application. I know that it has four endings (if I'm not mistaken) but really, these endings can only be triggered by specific choices. Basically what you choose to say in the first half of the game won't really affect the ending you'll get. Also, the acting and the voice acting was very disappointing. But really,  this game is actually fun and scary at the same time.
replyContent: Hi, just to clarify we utilize a weighted decision system. Which means there are choices that you make in the early game that will have a cumulative impact on what options are made available in the later game. On the voice and acting, we accept the critique and will do our best to improve it in out future games. Thank you for the review!

And even though I had already seen a playthough of It, I can easily say that I still got just as blown away and definitely jumpscared even harder than when watching Jack play.  It's what I usually say, horror movies are cool and all but keeping people on their toes can be hard because they're watching a story of a character that is in a situation that they cannot relate to. But horror games are in a different level because, even if you can't relate to the main character's situation, you are literally forced to be in that situation regardless because you play as them and everything is first person, which is WAAAAYYYY scarier.  Let me stop myself here before I ramble on for much longer. üòÇ What I'm trying to say is that this game is a masterpiece, perfectly made, loved every moment of it, it became one of my favourite games of all time and it's easily my favourite mobile game ever. (Even though I still do have some questions... ü§î but nothing that shakes from the fact that it was a genius game üòÖ)  It's a shame I can only give it 5 stars because I rate it 11/10.

This is a text adventure/creepy simulation game done RIGHT! Loved it. Wish there were more games like this. Loved the extensive use of apps, texts, emails, websites, pics, videos, and recordings. There is SO MUCH to explore which is a good thing. And it is all done incredibly realistically which is a GREAT thing. The sound effects are great. The tapping of phone keys can be heard as well as "YOUR" breathing!You can even like posts on the simulated Insta type app or swipe left/right on the simulated dating app. There are a TON of grammatical and spelling errors, but I told myself they were (hopefully!) intentional since it is texts/emails. Pretended that they were left in the game to make it more realistic. After awhile though, they do start to really stand out. Greg...man, Greg...one of his recordings is unintentionally hilarious. His voice, the way he overreacts, the words he chooses...comedy gold. Took me a little out of the game, but still nothing that diminishes game play. I actually listened to that message several times just to laugh. The pacing is perfect. I hate simulation games that force you to choose "fast" speed. This one does not do that. Instead, it moves exactly at the pace you move. No waiting around for texts or messages saying "Give me time" then waiting for hours. It is pretty much in real time which is AWESOME. Hints are well placed and not made too obvious. Depending on your replies/answers, you can pretty much choose your level of difficulty. It is easy to determine which reply or text will yield the info you may need to move forward. A lot of thought was put into this game. You can tell someone really cared about the little details, and that it was a labor of love. Please make more games like this. So much fun! Worth every penny!
replyContent: Hi Kristin, thank you for the awesome review. We  made sure to keep the grammatical and spelling errors to the chats and emails. There shouldn't be any errors in the official emails, websites and such. As you correctly guessed, it is meant to simulate real life chat conversations. Glad you enjoyed Greg :)
